{"id":"project-LICHEN-721x","title":"API contract violation: adapter_init accepts NULL ops despite _Nonnull","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1623-1635
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/include/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.h:271-272

The ops parameter is declared _Nonnull:
  void lichen_meshtastic_adapter_init(..., const struct lichen_meshtastic_adapter_ops *_Nonnull ops);

But the implementation explicitly handles NULL ops:
  if (ops != NULL) {
      adapter->ops = *ops;
  }

This is inconsistent. Callers may pass NULL expecting initialization to work (which it does), but static analyzers will flag this.

Fix: Either remove _Nonnull annotation or add assertion that ops != NULL.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:48:04.537539Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:48:04.537571Z"}

